      "span_text": "A second paper from this cohort has identified a low BMI in childhood as an important predictor of hip fracture in adulthood, suggesting a direct effect of low fat mass on bone mineralization, or an influence of altered timing of pubertal maturation.  The third piece of epidemiological evidence that osteoporosis might be programmed stems from mother-offspring studies.",
